procsynth.shine3.engine

Class Block

  • java.lang.Object
    • procsynth.shine3.engine.Block
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DummyAbstract, DummyFinal, DummyModule, DummyShine

    public class Block
extends Object
    A Block is a piece of program that has inputs and outputs. Blocks can by wired together through their inputs and outputs to form a complex program. There is two types of inputs or outputs : content and control. Types can be wired indifferently.
    Since:
    v0.0.1
    Author:
    procsynth - Antoine Pintout
    See Also:
    BlockEngine, BlockFactory
